item.description:
Peer to Peer skill session with a focus on paddling strokes, self and assisted rescue techniques, bracing, and edging kayaks. This is a PARTICIPATORY event. NO SPECTATORS! If you come, dress to be in the water! (the water is quite warm) You WILLÂ be wet exiting your boat on multiple occasions during the session, being the rescuee and the rescuer. This is an opportunity to learn/ practice safety and paddling technique that will improve your kayaking skills. Equipment: PFD, paddle, pump, paddle float, lunch, plenty of water! or non alcoholic beverages.

Location: Neal's Cove Boat Launch 11am Return to Launch Approx: 3:00 p.m.

Rain Date Sunday July 15
